      "B": "Bosniak III",
      "C": "Bosniak IV",
      "D": "Malignant tumor"
    },
    "answer": "A",
    "explanation": {
      "correct": "A hyperdense (>20 HU), well-marginated, non-enhancing renal cyst <3cm is classified as Bosniak II (benign). If >3cm, it is IIF.",
      "A": "Correct. Simple hyperdense cysts are Bosniak II.",
      "B": "Incorrect. Bosniak III requires thick walls or septations.",
      "C": "Incorrect. Bosniak IV requires enhancing soft tissue components.",
      "D": "Incorrect. Hyperdensity alone does not mean malignancy (often hemorrhage or protein).",
      "E": ""
    },
    "guideline": "Bosniak Classification 2019",
    "takeaway": "Hyperdense cysts are often benign but must be carefully evaluated for enhancement."
