    "question": "A 15-year-old boy has severe gastroenteritis with nausea, vomiting, and diarrhea for last 3 days. A CT scan of the abdomen shows intussusceptions, which needs exploratory laparotomy for relief of intestinal obstruction. The patient\u2019s systolic blood pressure is 78 mm Hg and heart rate is 112 bpm. Thiopental is selected as the induction agent for general anesthesia. A decreased dose of this agent is recommended in patients with hypovolemic shock primarily because",
