    "question": "A 75-year-old woman is scheduled for mitral valve repair. High-dose fentanyl is used to induce anesthesia. In order to counteract the bradycardia caused by fentanyl, pancuronium is administered. Pancuronium blocks the bradycardia caused by fentanyl by acting on which of the following?",
