  {
    "specialty": "HPB",
    "topic": "Acute Pancreatitis",
    "question": "A 45-year-old woman presents with severe epigastric pain radiating to the back, nausea, and vomiting. Serum lipase is 1500 U/L (Normal < 160). An ultrasound shows gallstones but no common bile duct dilation. Which of the following is the most important component of early management (first 24-48 hours)?",
    "options": {
