    "question": "A 55-year-old woman undergoes a core needle biopsy for a suspicious 1.5 cm mass in the upper outer quadrant of her left breast. The pathology shows Invasive Ductal Carcinoma, Grade 2, ER+/PR+, HER2-negative. Clinically, there are no palpable axillary nodes. What is the most appropriate surgical management for the axilla?",
