      "D": "Laparoscopic lavage is controversial and generally not the first choice for a drainable localized abscess.",
      "E": "Surgery should be delayed until the acute inflammation has resolved (usually 6-8 weeks) to allow for a safer, primary anastomosis."
    },
    "guideline": "ASCRS Clinical Practice Guidelines for the Management of Left-Sided Colonic Diverticulitis",
    "takeaway": "Key Concept: Diverticular abscesses > 3 cm (Hinchey Ib) should be managed with percutaneous drainage and antibiotics.",
