      "B": "",
      "C": "STK11 is associated with Peutz-Jeghers syndrome (hamartomatous polyps, mucosal pigmentation).",
      "D": "p53 is Li-Fraumeni syndrome (sarcomas, breast, brain tumors).",
      "E": "SMAD4 is associated with Juvenile Polyposis Syndrome."
    },
    "guideline": "NCCN Guidelines - Genetic/Familial High-Risk Assessment: Colorectal",
    "takeaway": "Key Concept: Lynch Syndrome (HNPCC) = MMR gene defect. Right-sided colon cancer + Endometrial cancer. Colonoscopy every 1-2 years starting at age 20-25.",
    "id": 808
  },
