    "question": "An 82-year-old woman presents with symptoms of small bowel obstruction. Her abdominal X-ray reveals 'Rigler's triad'. Which of the following correctly identifies the components of Rigler's triad and the most common site of the underlying problem?",
    "options": {
      "A": "Pneumobilia, small bowel obstruction, and an ectopic gallstone; Terminal ileum",
      "B": "Pneumoperitoneum, dilated stomach, and gallstones; Duodenum",
      "C": "Air in the portal vein, ascites, and a large gallbladder; Jejunum",
