    "question": "A 35-year-old woman presents with fecal incontinence following a difficult vaginal delivery with a 3rd-degree perineal tear. Anorectal manometry and endoanal ultrasound reveal a 120-degree defect in the external anal sphincter. What is the most appropriate surgical treatment?",
