    "question": "A patient presents with '6 Ps' of acute limb ischemia (Pain, Pallor, Pulselessness, Paresthesia, Paralysis, and Poikilothermia) in the right leg. An angiogram shows a 'cutoff' sign at the common femoral artery. What is the name of the catheter used for emergency embolectomy, and what is its mechanism?",
