    "specialty": "Pediatric Surgery",
    "topic": "Hirschsprung's Disease",
    "question": "A newborn fails to pass meconium in the first 48 hours and develops abdominal distension. An contrast enema shows a 'transition zone' in the rectosigmoid. What is the definitive diagnostic test for the suspected condition, and what is the characteristic pathological finding?",
    "options": {
