  },
  {
    "specialty": "General Surgery",
    "topic": "Pheochromocytoma",
    "question": "A 40-year-old female is scheduled for resection of a 4 cm right adrenal pheochromocytoma. Which of the following represents the correct sequence for preoperative pharmacological preparation?",
    "options": {
      "A": "Beta-blockade followed by alpha-blockade 2 weeks later",
