    "question": "A 40-year-old female presents with severe right upper quadrant pain radiating to the right shoulder after a fatty meal. It lasted 4 hours and resolved. Murphy's sign is negative. WBC and CRP are normal. Ultrasound shows gallstones. What is the diagnosis and management?",
